\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
Curriclum
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
by David Guenther
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
This specifies the education of a child, though colloboration with Church,
 School, and Homes.
 This outlines the relationship between the different content areas, and
 the process in which they are taught
\end_layout

\begin_layout Part*
Inner Core
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Taught by everyone, and central to the development of a child.
 This is the focus of Church
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Father
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Son
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Holy Spirit
\end_layout

\begin_layout Part*
Outer Core
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The knowledge of the Bible, which is the means in which we understand truth,
 and how we live in response to that truth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Truth
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
History
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Culture
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Culture is the set of practices and behavior outlined as norm.
 In the Christian Church, our culture is one of holiness and love.
 Such a culture is a result of our history, which in turn is a result of
 the truth of God's word.
 We must understand truth, and also how history has shown previous appliction
 of truth, to understand how to form the culture today.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is educated to children through their parents.
 The parents in turn receive this education from Church.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Part*
Mantle
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This knowledge is built upon our knowledge of the Word, and is the essential
 knowledge required for any profession.
\end_layout

